<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-08-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-08-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="125" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d125">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72111 Em 1/32½</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                President <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-08-10">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 10, 1915</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. President</hi>: I am in receipt of your
                            letter of yesterday in regard to the reply to the Austro-Hungarian
                            statement. I approve very heartily of the change which you made as to
                            the paragraph to be inserted on page 9. I will have our reply prepared
                            and sent as soon as possible, and also arrange for its publication here,
                            as I think it will have a salutary effect upon public opinion which is
                            undoubtedly being seriously affected by the propaganda against the
                            exportation of arms and ammunition.</p>
                        <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>